title: Solon beats Dubuque Wahlert 31-13, earns 3rd seed in 3A District 4
text:
Solon beats Dubuque Wahlert 31-13, earns 3rd seed in 3A District - KWWL - Eastern Iowa Breaking News, Weather, Closings Member Center: Solon beats Dubuque Wahlert 31-13, earns 3rd seed in 3A District 4 Posted: Friday Night Heroes Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> DUBUQUE (KWWL) - 
The Solon Spartans got off to a fast start, and would never look back. 
Solon's Spencer Lawson takes the Spartans' first play from scrimmage 71 yards to put them up 6-0 early. Wahlert would stuff the 2-point attempt. 
Solon looked much more methodical on their second drive, taking 13 plays to march down the field. Quarterback Brandon Childs takes the keeper up the middle to push the lead to 12-0. Another 2-point attempt thwarted by the Golden Eagles keeps the lead at 12. 
The Golden Eagles would force a fumble on a vicious hit, but that was about the only bright spot of their first half. 
In the 2nd, Childs hits Halston Durr with the beautiful over the should throw in the back of the end zone. The extra point makes it 19-0, and that would be the score at the half. 
In the second, Dubuque Wahlert would score on their first drive to make the score 19-7. After forcing a three and out, though, the Golden Eagles fumble the punt, and Solon promptly scores. Solon would also take an interception the other way for a touchdown in the second half. 
In the end, the Solon Spartans were just too much for Dubuque Wahlert, and they win 31-13. Solon claims the 3rd seed in the Class 3A District 4 playoffs with a record of 5-4 (4-2). Dubuque Wahlert claims the 4th seed, and finishes the regular season with a record of 3-6 (3-3).
